{title: Last Train To Heaven}
{artist: Boxcar Willie}
{composer: Written by Jan B. Shuster and Guy Henry Workman}

[C]I'll ride that [F]last train to heaven
On [C]rails of solid gold
In a [G7]boxcar lined with satin
Where the [F]nights are never [C]cold
Where a [F]hobo's always welcome
Even [C]in his ragged clothes
I'll [G7]ride that last train to heaven
When the [F]final whistle [C]blows
Well I set in hobo jungles
From [F]Maine to New Orleans
I've [G7]heard ole timers tell the tale
Of a [F]train they hope to [C]see
There'll be a long black steamer
That [F]shines just like the sun
With [G7]a thousand miles of boxcars
Be[F]hind engine number [C]one
Repeat #1,2
All the hobos will be waitin'
No [F]more sleepin' on the ground
With [G7]his hand upon the throttle
There'll [F]be no puttin' [C]down
This ride is just for hobos
They'll [F]come from all around
When [G7]that train gets down to her last run
[F]Destination heaven [C]bound